## Third-Party Protein Language Model Licenses

**IMPORTANT**: Modelomics provides interfaces to third-party protein language models.
**You are solely responsible** for obtaining, reviewing, and complying with all licenses
and terms of use for these models. The modelomics author(s) assume **NO LIABILITY** for
your use of these models or any violations of their terms.

### ESM-C Model (300M)

When using ESM-C embeddings via `embed_sequence(seq, model="esmc")`, you are subject to:

**License**: EvolutionaryScale Cambrian Open License Agreement  
**URL**: https://www.evolutionaryscale.ai/policies/cambrian-open-license-agreement

**Required Attribution**:
- Display "Built with ESM" on any API, model, workflow, website, UI, or documentation
- Identify any drug/molecular target as "Generated with ESM" in regulatory filings
- Include "ESM" at the beginning of derivative model titles
- Comply with ESM Acceptable Use Policy

**Restrictions**: Review the full license for commercial use restrictions and acceptable use policies.

### E1 Model (150M/300M/600M)

When using E1 embeddings via `embed_sequence(seq, model="e1")`, you are subject to:

**License**: Profluent-E1 Clickthrough License Agreement  
**Attribution Guidelines**: https://github.com/Profluent-AI/E1/blob/main/ATTRIBUTION  
**Full License**: https://github.com/Profluent-AI/E1/blob/main/LICENSE

**Required Attribution**:
- Display prominent attribution to "Profluent-E1" in all distributions and publications
- Identify any drug/molecular target as "Built with Profluent-E1" in regulatory filings
- For commercial use: attribution in main body of publications and title pages
- Attribution must be legible, properly sized, and not obscured

**Restrictions**: Review the full license for limitations and commercial use terms.

